	<!--
		[major].[minor].[revision] major version = HERAS-AF release -> (API
		changes on the main Interfaces (PDP,PIP,REPO etc.) or XACML Version
		change) minor version = Changes to the framework where the user is
		affected (e.g. indexer config file changes, repo internal core api
		changes, feature improvements) revision version = changes of
		implementations (internal bugfixes, patches, internal improvements
		etc.) Process: "top-down-propagation" = core version change propagates
		to Repo to repo-locator etc... (pseudo automatic, because updates in
		dependencies) Option for the future: User version ranges for
		dependency management (e.g repo needs a version of core between 2.5.0
		and 2.5.999)
	-->

